Load packages and function

library(openxlsx)
library(data.table)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(reshape2)
library(knitr)

is.nan.data.frame <- function(x)
  do.call(cbind, lapply(x, is.nan))

Import dataset

data<-read.table("~/OneDrive - UWM/Normalization paper Sept 2020/Data/Data_paper_HA.txt", sep = "\t", h=T)

Prepare dataset

# Count number of replicate assay per filter
N1N2.assay.count<-data %>% group_by(Sample_ID) %>% summarize(sum(!is.na(N1_avg)), .groups = 'drop'); names(N1N2.assay.count)[2]<-"N1N2_n_assay_per_filter"
data<-as.data.frame(setDT(N1N2.assay.count)[data, on="Sample_ID"])

# Count number of replicate filter per sample
filter.count<-data %>% group_by(CV) %>% summarize(n = length(unique(Sample_ID)), .groups = 'drop'); names(filter.count)[2]<-"n_filter"
data<-as.data.frame(setDT(filter.count)[data, on="CV"])

Pivot Table - only quantitative data

data.q<-subset(data, N1_LevelDetection=="Quantifiable")

assay.variability.q<- data.q %>% 
  group_by(City, Sample_ID, CV, Collection_Date_Start) %>%
  summarize(N1.avg = mean(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            N1.rsd = sd(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE)/mean(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop')
names(assay.variability.q)<-sub("[.]", "_", names(assay.variability.q)); names(assay.variability.q)<-sub("[.]", "_", names(assay.variability.q))
assay.variability.q$variability<-"assay"
assay.variability.comparison.q<-subset(assay.variability.q, N1_rsd!="NA")
assay.variability.comparison.q<-assay.variability.comparison.q[, c("City", "N1_rsd", "variability")]



filter.variability.q<-assay.variability.q %>%
  group_by(City, CV, Collection_Date_Start) %>%
  summarize(N1.avg = mean(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            N1.rsd = sd(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE)/mean(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop')
names(filter.variability.q)<-sub("[.]", "_", names(filter.variability.q)); names(filter.variability.q)<-sub("[.]", "_", names(filter.variability.q))
filter.variability.q$variability<-"filter"
filter.variability.comparison.q<-subset(filter.variability.q, N1_rsd!="NA")
filter.variability.comparison.q<-filter.variability.comparison.q[, c("City", "N1_rsd", "variability")]


day.to.day.variability.q<-filter.variability.q
day.to.day.variability.q$date <- as.Date(as.character(day.to.day.variability.q$Collection_Date_Start), format="%m/%d/%Y")
day.to.day.variability.q$week<-week(day.to.day.variability.q$date)
day.to.day.variability.q$weekday<-weekdays(day.to.day.variability.q$date)
day.to.day.variability.q<-subset(day.to.day.variability.q, weekday=="Sunday" | weekday=="Monday")
day.to.day.variability.q$comparison<-paste0(day.to.day.variability.q$City, "_", day.to.day.variability.q$week)
day.to.day.variability.q.final<-day.to.day.variability.q %>%
  group_by(comparison) %>%
  summarize(N1.avg = mean(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            N1.rsd = sd(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE)/mean(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop')
names(day.to.day.variability.q.final)<-sub("[.]", "_", names(day.to.day.variability.q.final)); names(day.to.day.variability.q.final)<-sub("[.]", "_", names(day.to.day.variability.q.final))
day.to.day.variability.q.final$variability<-"day-to-day (Sun-Mon)"
day.to.day.variability.q.comparison<-subset(day.to.day.variability.q.final, N1_rsd!="NA")
day.to.day.variability.q.comparison<-day.to.day.variability.q.comparison[, c("comparison", "N1_rsd", "variability")]
names(day.to.day.variability.q.comparison)[1]<-"City"

variability.comparison.q<-rbind(day.to.day.variability.q.comparison, assay.variability.comparison.q, filter.variability.comparison.q)
variability.comparison.q$variability <- ordered(variability.comparison.q$variability, levels = c("assay", "filter", "day-to-day (Sun-Mon)"))
variability.comparison.q$detection<-"quantifiable"

Values

variability.comparison.q %>%
  group_by(variability) %>% 
  summarize(mean = mean(N1_rsd, na.rm=TRUE),
            median = median(N1_rsd, na.rm=TRUE),
            sd = sd(N1_rsd, na.rm=TRUE),
            count = sum(!is.na(City)),
            .groups = 'drop')
## # A tibble: 3 x 5
##   variability           mean median    sd count
##   <ord>                <dbl>  <dbl> <dbl> <int>
## 1 assay                0.180  0.139 0.139   120
## 2 filter               0.238  0.208 0.178    83
## 3 day-to-day (Sun-Mon) 0.299  0.232 0.231    58
## Filter variability: below/above LOQ
mod1<-aov(sqrt(N1_rsd) ~ variability, data=subset(variability.comparison.q, N1_rsd != "NA")) 
summary(mod1)
##              Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value   Pr(>F)    
## variability   2  0.564 0.28179   8.267 0.000331 ***
## Residuals   258  8.795 0.03409                     
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
plot(mod1)

TukeyHSD(mod1)
##   Tukey multiple comparisons of means
##     95% family-wise confidence level
## 
## Fit: aov(formula = sqrt(N1_rsd) ~ variability, data = subset(variability.comparison.q, N1_rsd != "NA"))
## 
## $variability
##                                   diff           lwr       upr     p adj
## filter-assay                0.06277976  0.0006451978 0.1249143 0.0470324
## day-to-day (Sun-Mon)-assay  0.11625747  0.0466557066 0.1858592 0.0003114
## day-to-day (Sun-Mon)-filter 0.05347771 -0.0210077272 0.1279632 0.2100100

Plot

ggplot(variability.comparison.q, aes(x=variability, y=N1_rsd*100)) +
  geom_violin(trim=FALSE, fill='#bdded9', color="white", width=0.6) +
  geom_jitter(width=0.2) + 
  geom_boxplot(width=0.2) + 
  geom_hline(yintercept=25, linetype="dashed", color = "red") +
  theme_classic() + 
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size=14),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=15), 
        axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  labs(y = "Relative standard deviation (%)")

Comparison quantifiable vs BLQ

comparison<-rbind(variability.comparison.q, variability.comparison.blq)
comparison %>%
  group_by(variability, detection) %>% 
  summarize(mean = mean(N1_rsd, na.rm=TRUE),
            median = median(N1_rsd, na.rm=TRUE),
            count = sum(!is.na(City)),
            .groups = 'drop')
## # A tibble: 6 x 5
##   variability          detection     mean median count
##   <ord>                <chr>        <dbl>  <dbl> <int>
## 1 assay                blq          0.247  0.214    43
## 2 assay                quantifiable 0.180  0.139   120
## 3 filter               blq          0.217  0.138    32
## 4 filter               quantifiable 0.238  0.208    83
## 5 day-to-day (Sun-Mon) blq          0.271  0.216    23
## 6 day-to-day (Sun-Mon) quantifiable 0.299  0.232    58
## Assay variability: below/above LOQ
wilcox.test(N1_rsd ~ detection, data=subset(comparison, variability=="assay" & N1_rsd != "NA"), alternative = c("greater"))
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  N1_rsd by detection
## W = 3123, p-value = 0.02053
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is greater than 0
## Filter variability: below/above LOQ
wilcox.test(N1_rsd ~ detection, data=subset(comparison, variability=="filter" & N1_rsd != "NA"), alternative = c("two.side"))
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  N1_rsd by detection
## W = 1176, p-value = 0.3444
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
